                    <h2>WHAT ARE COOKIES AND HOW THEY ARE USED</h2>
                    <p>Cookies is a term that you may have heard a lot on the web recently. A cookie is a small file that asks for permission to be placed onto your computer's hard drive. After agreeing to this, the file is added and the cookie helps analyse all web traffic from that machine and/or lets you know when you have visited a particular site.</p>
                    <p>These cookies mean web applications can tailor what they display to you as an individual. This means that said applications can operate to your needs, likes and dislikes thanks to the information gathered from your preferences.</p>
                    <p>We use cookies that help identify which pages are in use, known as traffic log cookie. This means we can look at and analyse data about the traffic on our web page, tailoring pages to the needs of you, the customer. The data gathered is only used for statistical analysis purposes and after that it is then deleted from our system.</p>
                    <p>This means that, all in all, cookies help us give you a better end product and more pleasant experience on our website. Cookies do not grant us access into your computer in anyway, meaning the information about you, that you provide is the only information we have. As a general rule of thumb, web browsers will automatically accept cookies, but this can be changed within the browser settings. Ultimately meaning you have the choice of whether to accept or decline use of cookies. Declining their use may prevent you from taking full advantage of the website however.</p>
